# Fundamentals-of-AI-and-ML-Evaluated-Course-Project
A* Pathfinding in Python

Overview

This project is about the A* search algorithm. The A* search algorithm is used to find the path from a start position to a goal position in a grid-based maze. The A* search algorithm avoids walls. It uses a heuristic, which's the Manhattan distance to help the search.

Features

The project uses Pythons heapq to manage a priority queue for the A* search.

The A* search algorithm works with grid-based mazes that have walls and open paths.

The path is shown with symbols:

* S means Start

* G means Goal

* * means the path taken

* # means Wall

*. Means space

Requirements

You need Python 3.7 or a newer version.

You do not need any libraries just the built-in heapq.

Setup & Usage

To use this project you need to clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/a-star-maze.git

Then go to the a-star-maze directory:

cd a-star-maze

Now you can run the script:

python a_star.py

The program will show you the path coordinates from the start to the goal.

It will also show you a representation of the maze with the path marked.

Example Output

The path the agent takes is: [(0, 0) (1, 0) (2, 0) (2, 1) (2, 2) (3, 2) (4 2) (4, 3) (4, 4)]

The maze looks like this:

S #...

* #. #.

* * * #.

# # * #.

.. * * G

Customization

You can change the maze in the a_star.py file to try layouts.

You can change the start position and the goal position.

If you want to allow movement you can update the heuristic function to use the Euclidean distance.

Learning Notes

This project is good for learning about the A* search algorithm and pathfinding algorithms.

It is also good for learning about search and solving problems, on a grid.

The A* search algorithm is an algorithm to learn about.

Pathfinding algorithms are used in games and applications.

Heuristic search is a way to solve problems when you do not know the best solution.

Grid-based problem solving is a way to solve problems that can be represented on a grid.

The A* search algorithm is an example of a pathfinding algorithm
